SIMPLE: avoidable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Avoidable
<hw>A*void"a*ble</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Capable of being vacated; liable to be annulled or made invalid;
voidable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The charters were not <qex>avoidable</qex> for the king's
nonage.</q> <rj><qau>Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capable of being avoided, shunned, or
escaped.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Avoidance</ent>⟦br⟧
